  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><p class=\"passage_para\">A statistician constructed the 95&nbsp;percent confidence interval <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2.3 comma 3.7\"><math alttext=\"2.3 comma 3.7\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>2.3</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>‚Å¢</mo><mn>3.7</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> to estimate the slope of a regression model for a set of bivariate data with 24 data values.</p></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">If the sample size <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"n\"><math alttext=\"n\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> changes but all other things remain the same, which of the following claims about the confidence interval is true?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i4",
